snippet: A day of high-level meetings yielded little definite accomplishments, underscoring the many unresolved remaining issues between the two countries.
abstract: Sec of State John Kerry and Sec of Defense Chuck Hagel meet with their Russian counterparts to demonstrate that Pres Obama’s decision to cancel summit meeting with Pres Vladimir V Putin has not disrupted bilateral discussions on nuclear weapons, missile defense and regional issues.

byline.original: By THOM SHANKER and MICHAEL R. GORDON
byline.contributor: Steven Lee Myers contributed reporting from Moscow.

lead_paragraph: A day of high-level meetings yielded little definite accomplishments, underscoring the many unresolved remaining issues between the two countries.

headline.main: Kerry and Hagel Meet With Their Russian Counterparts
headline.print_headline: Kerry and Hagel Meet With Their Russian Counterparts
